  "prompt": "What's the difference between knitting and crocheting?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between knitting and crocheting:\n\nKnitting:\n- Uses two long needles\n- Creates loops and stitches with two active needles\n- Generally creates a more smooth, stretchy fabric\n- Usually done with thinner yarn\n- Typically faster for creating larger items like sweaters\n\nCrocheting:\n- Uses one hook\n- Creates stitches with a single hook, working one stitch at a time\n- Produces a thicker, more textured fabric\n- Can use thicker yarn\n- Often better for making more detailed/decorative items like doilies or amigurumi\n- Generally easier for beginners to learn\n\nBoth crafts involve creating fabric from yarn, but they have distinct techniques and end results.",
